    {
      "id": "E:note:row521238:1",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "54yo with PMH NASH, LBP, depression, anxiety, HTN, hypercholesterolemia    prese",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row521238#s1",
      "text": "54yo with PMH NASH, LBP, depression, anxiety, HTN, hypercholesterolemia    presents with increasing confusion, worsening hepatic encephalopathy;    in ED, treated for hyperkalemia with K+ 6.7 and intubated for airway    protection."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row521238:2",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Transfer to MICU for further care    Hepatic encephalopathy/NASH    Assessment: ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row521238#s2",
      "text": "Transfer to MICU for further care    Hepatic encephalopathy/NASH    Assessment:    Pt with NASH, remains intubated for airway protection, sedated on low    dose propofol; AMS complicated by pt s primary language Portuguese, pt    restless in bed; LFTs remain elevated but at baseline; on Bairhugger    Action:    Continues on Lactulose q2h, attempting to assess mental status; US at    bedside, marked site for tap; abx for ?"
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row521238:3",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "SBP; propofol increased to    20mcg/kg/min; attempted PS this am    Response:   ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row521238#s3",
      "text": "SBP; propofol increased to    20mcg/kg/min; attempted PS this am    Response:    No stooling with lactulose yet, soap suds enema given, remains    restless, unable to ascertain if pt is able to follow commands d/t    language barrier, pt not tracking; BP stable on propofol; o/u continue    marginal; OGT output guiac+ with small clots; did not tolerate PS    trial, became tachy to 110 s; US showing large volume ascites    Plan:    Trend WBC s, continue abx, follow-up culture data, continue mech vent    until mental status improves, may require liver bx, ? repeat tap; KUB    this am, holding lactulose for now"
    }
  ],
